ttp://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:23670:"<p>The Posts List Featured Image pro Addon is here. And we are off to a great start. While we will continue to update and include new features to the free version, as we see fit--we also intend on bringing enhanced features to the table in all of our Pro Addons. If you would like to know more about why we choose to use addons for our Pro releases, visit the <a title="Pro Addons" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/pro-addons/">Pro Addons</a> page.</p>\n<p><a title="List of Features" href="#listed-features"><strong style="font-size: 24px;">List of Features</strong></a> <a style=''text-decoration:none;'' href="javascript:void(null);" onclick="weaveriip_ToggleDIV(document.getElementById(''sh_67050368''), this, ''/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/open.png'', ''/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/close.png'', ''img'')"><img src="/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/open.png" alt="show" /></a></p><div id="sh_67050368"style="display:none;" >\n<ul>\n<li><span style="line-height: 1.5em;">Add, Remove, Change from post/page list Quick Edit feature</span></li>\n<li>Multi-Site Activation Support for Networks</li>\n<li>Add to Custom Post Type list pages (i.e. Events, Products, Properties, etc.)</li>\n<li>Auto set Featured Image to the first image that appears on the post</li>\n<li>Set a Global default Featured Image for posts with no images on them</li>\n<li>Bulk Edit Featured Image through Quick Edit (handy when used with sorting or filtering)</li>\n<li>Continued FREE Updates for the term of your license (e.g. we won''t make you upgrade your license if a new feature is added)</li>\n<li>Pro Level Support (includes: <a title="Pro Forum" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/pro-forum/">Pro Forum</a>, <a title="Submit Ticket" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/submit-ticket/">Support Tickets</a>, growing <a title="FAQs" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/faqs/">FAQs</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Future plans include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>function to set separate default Featured Images for each post type (i.e. Posts, Pages, Events, Products, Properties, etc.)</li>\n<li>function to recognize post types with videos and no images</li>\n<li>function to set default Featured Image for video posts</li>\n<li>And whatever else we or you can think of.</li>\n</ul>\n<p></p></div><p></p>\n<p><strong>Changelog</strong> <a style=''text-decoration:none;'' href="javascript:void(null);" onclick="weaveriip_ToggleDIV(document.getElementById(''sh_1812545446''), this, ''/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/open.png'', ''/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/close.png'', ''img'')"><img src="/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/open.png" alt="show" /></a></p><span id="sh_1812545446"style="display:none;" ><p><div id="per-page-widget" class="widget-area sidebar_extra per-page-changelog " style="margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;"><ul class="xoxo">\n<aside id="edd_sl_changelog_widget-2" class="widget widget_sl_changelog"><h3 class="widget-title">Changelog</h3><div class="edd_sl_changelog_widget" id="edd_sl_changelog_widget-2"><p>= 1.6.10 =<br />\n* fixed: parsing `post_content` throws a fatal error due to unescaped `&` - is now replaced by its html entity `&amp;`</p>\n<p>= 1.6.9 =<br />\n* changed: `simple_html_dom` library to `QueryPath`<br />\n* changed: now requires PHP &gt;= 5.4<br />\n* fixed: auto set featured image from remote URL does not get attached to the post<br />\n* tested: works with 4.6.1</p>\n<p>= 1.6.8 =<br />\n* tested with WP 4.6</p>\n<p>= 1.6.7 =<br />\n* tested with WP 4.5</p>\n<p>= 1.6.6 =<br />\n* fixed: addon doesn''t activate due to malformed data received from licensing server</p>\n<p>= 1.6.5 =<br />\n* changed: multisite options key<br />\n* fixed: license key does not activate for multisite installs</p>\n<p>= 1.6.4 =<br />\n* fixed: escape url attributes</p>\n<p>= 1.6.3 =<br />\n* added: install wp-cli script<br />\n* fixed: check for wp-cli support<br />\n* fixed: get_attachment_id_from_url method returning non-attachment id</p>\n<p>= 1.6.2 =<br />\n* moved: php version check to main plugin file<br />\n* changed: jquery-ui theme url</p>\n<p>= 1.6.1 =<br />\n* fixed: features not enabled for main site in multisite install</p>\n<p>= 1.6.0 =<br />\n* changed: file structure and code overhaul</p>\n<p>= 1.5.4 =<br />\n* fixed: plfi_pro_usage_instructions statements</p>\n<p>= 1.5.3 =<br />\n* optimized: license check</p>\n<p>= 1.5.2 =<br />\n* fixed: default post types (post, page) should now be ticked on plugin activation</p>\n<p>= 1.5.1 =<br />\n* fixed: unable to change post featured image after updating it in Quick Edit mode</p>\n<p>= 1.5.0 =<br />\n* added: featured image auto set and cancel auto set buttons with toggle script.<br />\n* added: auto set first image from post content as featured image.<br />\n* added: settings input field for default featured image<br />\n* added: media library dialog to pick default featured image.<br />\n* fixed: license status key transient data which doesn''t get set properly upon license (de)activate<br />\n* moved: JavaScript and styles to external files.<br />\n* moved: settings page script to external js file (plfi-pro-settings-script.js)<br />\n* optimized: update/delete featured image.</p>\n<p>= 1.4.2 =<br />\n* fixed: a script error that prevents the preview image to not be displayed when thumbnail js object is undefined</p>\n<p>= 1.4.1 =<br />\n* fixed: warning notice generated by empty variable of post types fetched from options table</p>\n<p>= 1.4.0 =<br />\n* added: support for custom post types<br />\n* fixed: undefined index notice displayed when creating a new post<br />\n* fixed: incorrect featured image id fetched when quick editing<br />\n* fixed: media uploader style rule for unneeded elements</p>\n<p>= 1.3.2 =<br />\n* fixed: incorrect/unused license check variable in run_addon_features method<br />\n* fixed: license not properly validating</p>\n<p>= 1.3.1 =<br />\n* fixed: license key (de)activation button when saving from options page.</p>\n<p>= 1.3.0 =<br />\n* fixed: remove image when doing bulk edit after setting featured image in quick edit<br />\n* fixed: update license key in options table when (de)activating license</p>\n<p>= 1.2.0 =<br />\n* fixed: remove image when doing bulk edit after setting featured image in quick edit</p>\n<p>= 1.0.0 =<br />\n* Initial release.</p>\n</div></aside>\n</ul></div>\n</p></span><p></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/mnVhB2rhSLk?list=UUisaL7QfbcOKwdhqW12MVKQ" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>\n<p>We have made managing your posts featured images even more convenient than ever before.</p>\n<p>You will need the Free basic version of <a id="listed-features" title="FREE Post List Featured Image" href="http://wordpress.org/plugins/post-list-featured-image/" target="_blank">Posts List Featured Image</a> for the Pro Addon to work. So if you haven''t grabbed it yet, go install it one your WordPress site, and give it a test run. Once you fall in love with it, as we know you will, go to the settings page and order the <strong>Posts List Featured Image Pro Addon</strong>.</p>\n<h3>Features</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><span style="line-height: 1.5em;">Add, Remove, Change from post/page list Quick Edit feature</span></li>\n<li>Add to Custom Post Type list pages (i.e. Events, Products, Properties, etc.)</li>\n<li>Auto set Featured Image to the first image that appears on the post</li>\n<li>Set a Global default Featured Image for posts with no images on them</li>\n<li>Bulk Edit Featured Image through Quick Edit (handy when used with sorting or filtering)</li>\n<li>Continued FREE Updates for the term of your license (e.g. we won''t make you upgrade your license if a new feature is added)</li>\n<li>Pro Level Support (includes: <a title="Pro Forum" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/pro-forum/">Pro Forum</a>, <a title="Submit Ticket" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/submit-ticket/">Support Tickets</a>, growing <a title="FAQs" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/faqs/">FAQs</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Future plans include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>function to set separate default Featured Images for each post type (i.e. Posts, Pages, Events, Products, Properties, etc.)</li>\n<li>function to recognize post types with videos and no images</li>\n<li>function to set default Featured Image for video posts</li>\n<li>And whatever else we or you can think of.</li>\n</ul>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/pro-plugins-shop/"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-242" title="Posts List Featured Image Pro Addon" src="http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/posts-list-featured-image-pro-addon.png" alt="Posts List Featured Image Pro Addon" width="713" height="317" srcset="http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/posts-list-featured-image-pro-addon.png 713w, http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/posts-list-featured-image-pro-addon-300x133.png 300w, http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/posts-list-featured-image-pro-addon-100x44.png 100w, http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/posts-list-featured-image-pro-addon-500x222.png 500w" sizes="(max-width: 713px) 100vw, 713px" /></a></p>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\r\n\r\n<table style="background: #fefefe;box-shadow: 0 0 40px #ccc;border-radius: 10px;">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;" colspan="4">\r\n<h2><strong>Post List Featured Image Pro Addon</strong></h2>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>Single Site</strong></td>\r\n<td style="text-align: center; border-right-width: 1px; border-right-style: solid; border-left-width: 1px; border-left-style: solid;"><strong>3 - Sites License</strong></td>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>10 - Sites License</strong></td>\r\n<td style="text-align: left; width: 42%;" rowspan="6">	<form id="edd_purchase_407" class="edd_download_purchase_form edd_purchase_40