ess Admin panel and navigate to the Plugins list page.</li>\n<li>Activate the Posts List Featured Image plugin</li>\n<li>Enjoy viewing the list of featured images now appearing on your Posts List page.</li>\n</ol>\n<hr />\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/plugins/post-list-featured-image/" target="_blank"><img id="dl-btn" class=" wp-image-99 alignnone" title="Posts List Featured Image Plugin Dowload" src="http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/downlaod-btn-green.png" alt="Posts List Featured Image Plugin Download" width="275" height="100" /></a></p>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n<h3>Topic | WordPress Plugin - Posts List Featured Image</h3>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/plugins/posts-list-featured-image/">Posts List Featured Image &#8211; WordPress Plugin</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com">Jagged Edge Media</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:23:"HostGator Crashed Again";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:56:"http://jaggededgemedia.com/blog/hostgator-crashed-again/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 17 Apr 2014 08:13:29 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Blog";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"crash";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"hostgator";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"hosting company";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"server down";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:34:"http://jaggededgemedia.com/?p=1744";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:570:"<p>As of the time of this post, HostGator Crashed again has been down for most of the previous day. Some of you, who have remained loyal to HostGator, may remember the mass outage last year, August 2, 2013, when Hostgator changed data &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/blog/hostgator-crashed-again/">Read More >></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/blog/hostgator-crashed-again/">HostGator Crashed Again</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com">Jagged Edge Media</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Johnny Akzam";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3914:"<p><a href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/hostgator.png"><img class="alignleft wp-image-1747 size-full" src="http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/hostgator.png" alt="Hostgator Crashed Again" width="180" height="180" srcset="http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/hostgator.png 180w, http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/hostgator-150x150.png 150w" sizes="(max-width: 180px) 100vw, 180px" /></a>As of the time of this post, <strong>HostGator Crashed a</strong>gain has been down for most of the previous day. Some of you, who have remained loyal to HostGator, may remember the mass outage last year, August 2, 2013, when Hostgator changed data centers to the current one. The company that bought out HostGator, Endurance International Group, issued a statement in a blog response they set up to address the frantic customers looking for answers:</p>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n<blockquote><p>During the morning of August 2, 2013, Endurance International Group’s data center in Provo, UT experienced unexpected issues that impacted customers of bluehost, HostGator, HostMonster and JustHost. Company websites and some phone services were affected as well.</p>\n<p>Many of our customers’ sites are back online. Some customers may continue to experience intermittent access and slowness until services are fully restored. Customer should not experience any loss of data.</p>\n<p>The resources of our entire company are focused on the recovery, including our executive team, which is leading these efforts from our command center in Burlington, MA. The team will issue updates at enduranceresponse.com every 30 minutes until all customer services are restored. Following the restoration of services, Endurance will conduct a thorough review of this incident.</p></blockquote>\n<p>For those of us that took that as a sign of things to come and got out when we could, we are happily posting away on our websites. For those of you that did not heed the warning, I can only say, NOW IS THE TIME TO GET OUT!</p>\n<p>Now that Hostgator Crashed again, these outages are not just effecting a couple servers, intermittently. They are crashing hundreds of thousands to millions of sites in one fell swoop. Two of our current clients are being effected by this outage, and there is absolutely nothing they can do about it. All anyone can do is site and wait, like stranded boats in the vast ocean that is HostGator support.</p>\n<p>This is the second mass outage in just over 8 months. One a year is way too many. not only can outages of this nature cost its site owners millions in potential revenue, it can have a "network" affect on a mass of users that do not use the downed hosting provider. For instance, if Jagged Edge Media still used HostGator, then the licenses we issue for our products would fail to work upon the next check, after the outage. As a matter of fact, one of our friends and a recommended plugin have been affected by the outage, thus affecting our license for the plugin.</p>\n<p>If you have been effected by this outage, please comment on this post and click a rating star. Let''s put a stop to the madness. I now host with <strong><a title="Site5" href="http://www.site5.com/in.php?id=189590" target="_blank">Site5</a></strong>. And they are pretty good. I am always looking into other options, and now that one of my clients is determined to leave Hostgator for good, I am looking around again. One valid prospect is <strong><a title="GeekStorage hosting" href="http://www.geekstorage.com/aff/785" target="_blank">GeekStorage</a>.</strong></p>\n<h3>Topic: Hostgator Crashed Again on April 16, 2014</h3>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/blog/hostgator-crashed-again/">HostGator Crashed Again</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com">Jagged Edge Media</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:33:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"Gravity Forms WordPress Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17: