	\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"WordPress Development Redefined";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:64:"http://jaggededgemedia.com/blog/wordpress-development-redefined/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 11 Mar 2014 14:59:24 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Blog";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:34:"http://jaggededgemedia.com/?p=1313";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:633:"<p>WordPress Development Redefined I would like to welcome you to our new stage for WordPress Development and the ongoing growth of technology, through the collaboration and communication among those, who strive for a better online experience for developers and users alike. &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/blog/wordpress-development-redefined/">Read More >></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/blog/wordpress-development-redefined/">WordPress Development Redefined</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com">Jagged Edge Media</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Johnny Akzam";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4381:"<h2>WordPress Development Redefined</h2>\n<p>I would like to welcome you to our new stage for WordPress Development and the ongoing growth of technology, through the collaboration and communication among those, who strive for a better online experience for developers and users alike. There is no other CMS out there right now that offers the flexibility, usability, and reliability found through WordPress.</p>\n<p>With a vast array of Themes and Plugins, we have found that developing a website on WordPress can provide the same--if not better--experience than those found on sites that cost in the tens of thousands of dollars.</p>\n<div id="attachment_67" style="width: 782px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/plugins/post-list-featured-image/"><img class="size-full wp-image-67" alt="Post List Featured Image" src="http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/dynamic-image1.png" width="772" height="250" srcset="http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/dynamic-image1.png 772w, http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/dynamic-image1-300x97.png 300w, http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/dynamic-image1-500x161.png 500w" sizes="(max-width: 772px) 100vw, 772px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Get Our FREE Plugin</p></div>\n<p>So what do you need to start your WordPress Development? if you have nothing, then all you need is a domain name and hosting, which we provide. If you have a website already, then you will likely have a hosting account or at least know who you are paying for that service. If your site is not a WordPress site already, then you will need to have access to that hosting account. JEM offers hosting at a reduced cost. We operate on a dedicated server. That means we have complete control over our system. However, that does not mean that we maintain control over your account.</p>\n<p>It is our belief that the clients and users should maintain full control over the assets they pay for. We are well aware of the horror stories of unsuspecting clients that have left everything up to the developers. Then, if they wish to end that relationship, the developers hold their website hostage. We are not interested in owning your site or controlling your files or data. As a matter of fact, it is our hope that you will soon be able to administer your own site at will.</p>\n<p><span style="background-color: #eef2f2;"><cite title="Hosting Change">[Update:] Due to Hostgator''s recent changes to a new Data Center, in August of 2013, which has lead to a number of outages, unreliable structure, loss of Support integrity, among other factors, we no longer recommend the service as our top model for a Hosting Solution. In fact, JAcom, the parent company of JEM, will have moved to a new hosting solution and company by mid-December 2013.<br />\nWe will update our loyal users and followers, after we have had a chance to evaluate the new service.</cite></span></p>\n<p><del>JEM strives to be completely transparent. We host through Hostgator. That is the service we recommend. Even if you do not choose to host with us, we will help you save on your first payment with a 25% discount coupon on your account with Hostgator, and even help with the transfer of your current website.</del></p>\n<p>We will always be here for major support of the WordPress Development. But the day to day tasks involved in maintaining your website should be left to you and your office. We will only share what we believe are the best of the best of services and resources for your web marketing campaign.</p>\n<p>The JEM.com website is constantly updating to bring you some of the latest in WP News. However, you can find our plugins list on the <a title="PLUGINS" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/plugins/">Plugins page</a>.</p>\n<p>If you wish to hire us for your projects, feel free to <a title="Contact Us" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/contact-us/">Contact Us</a> for a free evaluation of your project and a quote.</p>\n<p><span style="line-height: 1.4em;">There will be much more to come shortly.</span></p>\n<h3>Topic: WordPress Development Redefined</h3>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/blog/wordpress-development-redefined/">WordPress Development Redefined</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com">Jagged Edge Media</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:36:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:36:"PHPStorm IDE – Beyond The Language";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:45:"http://jaggededgemedia.com/blog/phpstorm-ide/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 16 Jan 2014 21:16:29 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Blog";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Our Tools";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:34:"http://jaggededgemedia.com/?p=1064";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:540:"<p>Johnny''s 50 cents: Hear what I think about PHPStorm IDE. As part of our dedication to users and fellow developers, we like to take a moment from time to time to tell you about some of the feature services and &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/blog/phpstorm-ide/">Read More >></a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/blog/phpstorm-ide/">PHPStorm IDE &#8211; Beyond The Language</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com">Jagged Edge Media</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Johnny Akzam";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4013:"<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.jetbrains.com/phpstorm/" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-1065" src="http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/phpstorm_logo.gif" alt="phpstorm_logo" width="720" height="162" /></a>Johnny''s 50 cents:</p>\n<p>Hear what I think about PHPStorm IDE. As part of our dedication to users and fellow developers, we like to take a moment from time to time to tell you about some of the feature services and tools we use on a daily basis to run our platform and develop our plugins for you.</p>\n<p>It should come as no surprise that the folks at <a title="JetBrains" href="http://www.jetbrains.com/company/index.html" target="_blank">JetBrains</a> have a complete solution for the coder in your life. With their <a title="JetBrains Awards" href="http://www.jetbrains.com/company/press/awards.html" target="_blank">Award Winning</a> software and programs to serve the technological world. I am personally the lesser of the two code mongers  I handle the main CSS, PHP and HTML, while Paul handles the really cool stuff. However, because of the outstanding way PHPStorm handles its deployment interface, we have no real need for a separate repo for our commercial Pro plugins. If I make any changes to the development site files, Paul will know, then next time he opens his connected PHPStorm.</p>\n<p>Not only can we work in unison, as a team, but we don''t lose any time searching through code, looking for changes. <a title="PHPStorm IDE" href="http://www.jetbrains.com/phpstorm/whatsnew/" target="_blank">PHPStorm IDE</a> makes our lives easier, cutting the development time down, which means we can push out updates faster for the users and save you money.</p>\n<p>Also, because I am now venturing into the more involved coding languages like Javascript, Backbone.js, and JQuery.js, <a title="PHPStorm IDE" href="http://www.jetbrains.com/phpstorm/" target="_blank">PHPStorm IDE has features</a> that will help me collaborate with other development projects, in a more professional way.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Paul''s 50 cents:</p>\n<p><a href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/ps8.png"><img class="alignleft wp-image-2629 size-medium" src="http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/ps8-300x250.png" alt="" width="300" height="250" srcset="http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/ps8-300x250.png 300w, http://jaggededgemedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/ps8.png 336w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a>Out of all the code editors I''ve tried, PHPStorm stood out best. I have lots of options in configuring my code styles, just the way I like them to look. Often times, I use an external command line for version control stuff, BUT they have that in the editor itself, so that''s cool. It has file and code templates, which is really handy, especially when I create new files of the same format and/or codes.</p>\n<p>In actually writing the code, I get a lot of helpers that ease typing, like the live templates, which allows me to type an abbreviation of the code and press the "expand" button I''ve set for it. Then it automatically fills in the common declaration or code. Another thing, is the availability of version control within the editor apart from the command line tool. I can do a lot of the basic stuff with just "point-and-click" to run a command.</p>\n<p>There are still a lot of features in PHPStorm that I have yet to try, and I believe with the community that''s using it, it''s highly likely to get more features and even get better and better with every product updates.</p>\n<p>Together, that makes an even buck. What are your thoughts? Please leave a comment. We encourage your input and feedback.</p>\n<h3>Topic: PHPStorm IDE - Beyond the Language</h3>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com/blog/phpstorm-ide/">PHPStorm IDE &#8211; Beyond The Language</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://jaggededgemedia.com">Jagged Edge Media</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:33:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:24:"PLFI Pro Addon Changelog";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59:"http://jaggededgemedia.com/addons/plfi-pro-addon-changelog/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sun, 22 Dec 2013 18:04:27 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"Addons";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:34:"http://jaggededgemedia.com/?p=1044";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8: